docs.text: it's been a long time since walt disney has delivered us a classic along the lines of the little mermaid or beauty and the beast .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sure , there have been delightful outings like last years hercules .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but nothing entirely groundbreaking .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: with the release of the studio's newest feature length film , a remake of edgar rice burrough's creation tarzan , disney has plunged into new waters with both maturity and animation techniques .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's no classic , but this new tarzan represents exactly what a family film should be .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the plot is loyal to the original storyline , as tarzan's parents are forced to abandon their ship which has caught fire , and find shelter in the jungles of africa .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but , they are killed ( offscreen ) by the snarling cheetah sabor , leaving baby tarzan alone and unharmed in his crib .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: found by kala ( voiced with effective gentleness by glenn close ) , a kindhearted mother and member of a gorilla pack , tarzan is taken into the primate group and raised as one of their own .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we follow the young boy through the years , as he partakes in various adventures with his loud mouth gorilla friend terk ( a very brash but funny rosie o'donnell ) and clumsy elephant tantor ( wayne knight ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of course , in any disney film we are given some kind of goofy sidekick or humorous chum for the hero .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in tarzan , these characters fill that space rather inconspicuously .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: gags that were magnified in other family films are kept quite minor here .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: most of the characters are amusing without being forced .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as tarzan grows to manhood , the suspected antagonist stumbles into the picture .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: here , the notorious bad guy is the big game hunter clayton ( brian blessed ) , who's accompanying a hapless professor ( nigel hawthorne ) on an expedition through the jungle .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of course , there's the professor's daughter , jane ( nicely vocalized by a cheerful minnie driver ) who will help supply the romantic quotient of the movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the thing that blew my socks off about this version of tarzan is the stunning animation .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: directors chris buck and kevin lima have applied a breathtaking 3-d element to the movement of the athletic title character , and the fast-paced editing is absolutely a marvel .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as tarzan carries jane through the treetops , narrowly escaping a pack of nasty baboons , he slips and slides like a daredevil snow boarder or star surfer riding the big wave .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: your eyes can barely keep up ; it's a fantastic accomplishment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the subject matter here is also a notch or two above animation average .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are important questions raised about tarzan's place in the world , and all are handled exceptionally well by the screenwriters .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is no shred of doubt left to ponder afterward , which is a surprising plus that i wasn't expecting to find here .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: suffice to say , this film will have both adults and children thoroughly entertained .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the grown-up tarzan is voiced by tony goldwyn , who made a name for himself as the `big mean jerk' from ghost .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: goldwyn is effective playing someone who's not aware of his world's dangers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: glenn close is also memorable as his gorilla mother , and lance henriksen ( from tv's millennium ) is terrific as the silverback father unsure of how to accept the presence of a human child .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as the movie's villain , there is nothing particularly special or catching about the character of clayton .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it helps that brian blessed supplies his voice with game enthusiasm , but he is nothing compared to james woods' hilarious hades from hercules .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a burley guy with a big gun who just wants to capture the gorillas does not quite constitute for an all-together noticeable screen presence .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: still , this is one great thrill-ride that disney has constructed .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i never expected rice burrough's work to be transformed so successfully from live action to animation , nor with so much emotional depth .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: parents , along with all the kiddies , are going to find much to like in tarzan .
docs.label: positive
